Merge pull request #9 from eagletmt/retry-load-secret

Retry when org.freedesktop.Secret.Item.GetSecret fails

Retry when org.freedesktop.Secret.Item.GetSecret fails

It occasionally fails with a message "** Message: received an invalid or
unencryptable secret".
In my environment, `for i in $(seq 1000); do envchain aws true; done`
will print the message about 3-8 times.

My solution is to retry 3 times if such an error is detected.

= New feature

- Linux support with libsecret (#7 @eagletmt)

  libsecret commuicates with D-Bus secret service; for instance,
  gnome-keyring implements it.

= New feature in v0.2.0 (forgot to note..)

- `--list` command

  On OS X keychain, values have to be set after envchain v0.2.0 or later
  due to data structure change, in prior to be listed.
